%N A394789 Number of positive integers <= n with exactly two odd divisors.
%C A394789 a(n) is also the number of positive integers <= n with two partitions into consecutive parts.
%C A394789 a(n) is also the number of positive integers m <= n whose symmetric representation of sigma(m) has two subparts.
%e A394789 The first number with two odd divisors is 3 so a(3) = 1.
%e A394789 4 has only one odd divisor so a(4) = a(3) = 1.
%e A394789 The second number with two odd divisors is 5 so a(5) = 2.
%e A394789 The third number with two odd divisors is 6 so a(6) = 3.
%e A394789 The two partitions of 3 into consecutive parts are [3], [2, 1].
%e A394789 The two partitions of 5 into consecutive parts are [5], [3, 2].
%e A394789 The two partitions of 6 into consecutive parts are [6], [3, 2, 1].
%t A394789 seq[n_] := Accumulate[Table[Boole[DivisorSigma[0, k/2^IntegerExponent[k, 2]] == 2], {k, 1, n}]]; seq[100] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 03 2026 *)
%o A394789 (Python)
%o A394789 from sympy import primepi
%o A394789 def A394789(n): return -(m:=n.bit_length()-1)+sum(primepi(n>>i) for i in range(m)) # _Chai Wah Wu_, Apr 13 2026
